<p><font>Closing line from John Marston's
        masque: <em>The Entertainment of Alice, Dowager-Countess
        of Derby</em>. Niobe is often equated with 'fallen towers',
	usually Rome, but here a simile with Venice is drawn. The
	cabinet is the actual poem, which is, like the cabinet in
	Poe's short story "The Assignation", a medley of 
	architectural embellishments. </font></p>
